<h3><a name="quests">Monk Quests</a></h3><br>
<b><a name="mq1">Q: Is Brother Qwinn broken?</a></b><br>
<br>
A: Probably not. It's not at all unheard of for Qwinn to go long periods without spawning, especially when there's a lot of patching going on. Since he has no PH that we're aware of, you'll just have to park in SK and/or bother someone with tracking. If a Guide or GM tells you he's on vacation, or is broken, chances are that they're just not familiar with how the quest/NPC works, and is making something up.  Note:  a recent patch (January 23) increased Qwinn's spawn rate, so he should be less of a problem now.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<b><a name="mq2">Q: How do I get the Ancient Cyclops to spawn for JBoots?</a></b><br>
<br>
A: Check out the guide <a href="http://pub38.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showMessage?topicID=494.topic" target=new>here</a>.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<b><a name="mq3">Q: Is Trunt/Eejag/Raster/Zephyl/whatever doable with this group/solo?</a></b><br>
<br>
A: Depends on group layout/your equipment.  Statistics and abilities of the mobs are posted in various threads and guides, it should be easy for you to figure out on yourself how much power you need for what mob.  <a href="http://pub38.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showMessage?topicID=618.topic" target=new>Keyeluke's guide on Zephyl ganking</a> will help you here, and <a href="http://www.monkly-business.com/articles.asp?ArticleId=1" target=new>Bodi's Epic Guides</a> will help you with the others.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<b><a name="mq4">Q: Can I kill Brother Zephyl and Brother Qwinn for the Robe of the Lost Circle?</a></b><br>
<br>
A: Yes, you can; however, they don't drop it every time.  Also, they won't always appear to be wearing it, even if they have it -- if you zoned in after they spawn, they won't show as wearing it.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<b><a name="mq5">Q: <i>Should</i> I kill Brother Zephyl or Brother Qwinn for my RotLC?</a></b><br>
<br>
A: Please don't kill Qwinn.  He's hard enough to find without people killing him, and Zephyl is easy to spawn.  If you want to kill Zephyl, go right ahead. It's up to you whether you want to spend the time camping Raster/Targin, or kill Bro Z. Nobody cares how you get your epic (as long as you don't kill Qwinn), so long as you're honorable about it towards other players. Posting this question on MB serves only to create flame wars. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
