<h3><a name="monkeq">Monk Equipment</a></h3><br>
<b><a name="me1a"></a>Q:  Is FBSS haste 17% or 21%?</b><br>
<br>
A: There are 2 ways to measure haste. The first, and most generally used measure is of how much the haste increases the number of times you hit. The other measure is of how much the haste will decrease your weapon delay.<p><br>
<br>
The two measures are related in this way:<p><br>
<br>
% increase of number of times you hit = <b>a</b><br>
<br>
% decrease in weapon delay = <b>b</b><p><br>
<br>
(1-[100/(100+<b>a</b>)]) X 100% = <b>b</b><p><br>
<br>
If we use this for the FBSS, we get (1-[100/(100+<b>21</b>)]) X 100% = <b>17%</b><p><br>
<br>
So we see how FBSS will decrease your weapon delay by 17% and increase the number of times you hit by 21%.<br>
<br>
<br>
<b><a name="me1"></a>Q: How does haste stacking work?</b><br>
<br>
A: There are 5 types of haste for purposes of stacking:<br>
<br>
1. Item Haste - e.g. that gained from wearing an item with the 'haste' effect on it. Such items include FBSS, Runed Bolster Belt, Cloak of Flames.<br>
<br>
2. Spell/Song Haste - e.g. that gained from either having a haste spell cast on you, or a bard song playing. This category includes the effect on the Robe of the Whistling Fists and the Celestial Fists and also the clickable effect on the Eyepatch of Plunder.<br>
<br>
3. Ervaj songs - There are 2 bard songs (a 5% one at 50, and a 10% one at 60) which stack on top of item and other spell/song haste but cannot go over the haste cap<br>
<br>
4. Vah Shir songs - Stack with item and all other song hastes and allow group members to go over the haste cap. <br>
<br>
5. Monk Discipline - 100 fist - stacks with everything<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
There are Haste Caps (for monks)of:<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
85% (< lev 51)<br>
<br>
100% (51 - 60)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Some examples:<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Some combos (with haste granted to clarify) assumed level 51+ for purpose of capping.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
1) FBSS (21%) + RoTWF (25%) = 46%<br>
<br>
2) FBSS (21%) + Epic (40%) = 61%<br>
<br>
3) FBSS (21%) + Speed of the Shissar (66%) = 87%<br>
<br>
4) FBSS (21%) + Shissar (66%) + Epic (40%) = 87%<br>
<br>
(note epic haste does not stack with shissar haste, however the<br>
<br>
ATK/AC boost elements do stack)<br>
<br>
5) Golden Sash of Tranquility (41%) + Shissar (66%) = 100% (haste is capped at a maximum of 100)<br>
<br>
6) SoTD (24%) + Shissar (66%) + Composition of Ervaj (10%) =100%, since Ervaj doesn't bring you over the cap.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
There are only 2 ways to exceed the haste cap of 100%:<br>
<br>
1) High level bard songs (e.g. Warsong of the Vah Shir - 25% haste) will stack with other spell hastes to take you to 125% <br>
<br>
2) 100 fist discipline ignores the haste cap and stacks with all other hastes in the game. Supposed 20%.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Max Haste Solo:<br>
<br>
41% haste item + 40% from epic= 81% (+ 20% from 100 fists if disc active)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Max Haste Grouped:<br>
<br>
41% haste item + Chanter/Bard Song Haste > 59% (eg. Shissar) + Warsong of the Vah Shir (25% stackable)= 125% (+ 20% from 100 fists if disc active).<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<b><a name="me2"></a>Q: Do Holgresh Elder Beads still drop?</b><br>
<br>
A: No, they don't. Not that there's as much use for them nowadays, since they've been nerfed not to get aggro at all.  That said, there's a drop from the stone spider in SolB that has 5 charges of Eye of Zomm, as well as a tinkered piece called Stalking Probes that takes 106 tinkering skill to trivial and costs 16pp in components.  Make friends with a gnome today!<br>
