<b><a name="me8"></a>Q: What's pumice, and where can I get some?</b><br>
<br>
A: Crystallized Pumice is a 0.8wt, non-stackable, merchant-bought item that has 5 charges of Nullify Magic (a spell that removes the top 2 buffs an enemy has, for a 2.0second casting time). It's an invaluable tool for soloing, since you can pumice away SoW and damage shields on enemies and DoTs on yourself. It costs about 12pp, and is sold at any herb vendor (Ask your local alchemist. they'll know where the herb vendors are.)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<b><a name="me9"></a>Q: I attacked a Wisp and a Ghoul and every attack said "You punch a Ghoul but it is INVULNERABLE" why can't I do damage to these monsters?</b><br>
<br>
A: Wisps, Ghouls and some other creatures require magic weapons to hit and do damage to them. At level 30 your fists become magical weapons, but until then you will need to obtain magical gloves to fight these creatures. Some gloves available are Wu's Fighting Guantlets(Tailor Created), Mesh Gloves(Frogloks in Guk and Qeynos Sewers), Treant Fists(Quest) All special attacks (except Kick) are magical too. However, the "kick" at the end of Instill Doubt is not -- so you need magic shoes to be able to successfully ID magic-damage-only monsters.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
