<b><a name="gt2"></a>Q: What is "Tag Pulling"?</b><br>
<br>
A: Tag Pulling, also known as Chain Pulling, is different from, and yet similar to, chain aggro. Instead of each mob being triggered by the previous mob, players take turns triggering each other. <br>
<br>
If a mob is particularly dangerous, or the group camp spot is particularly far away, and it is unlikely that a single puller could bring this mob that far without dying, tag pulling is often used. Multiple pullers, usually all with the ability to Feign Death, either through spells or abilities, help bring the mob or mobs to the group. The first puller will aggro the mob and begin to run back to the group. When they reach a certain spot, or get too low on life, they will use Feign Death. The second puller stays back out of aggro range and has two choices. They can aggro all the mobs the first puller brought, or they can wait for some of them to wander off before pulling just a subset of them. There can be as many "legs" of a pull as necessary to cover the distance back to the group. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<b><a name="gt3"></a>Q: I am an Iksar, how do I raise faction so I can bank in (Insert city here)?</b><br>
