<b><a name="sns4"></a>Q: What breaks a successful Feign?</b><br>
<br>
A: Two things will break a sucessful feign: (1) getting hit by any spell except a dispell, beneficial or harmful, including AEs, and (2) moving.  There are lots of things that could make you move while FD -- steep slopes, accidentally right-clicking on a corpse (and thereby looting it) when you're trying to con a mob, or finishing a bandage all count as movement.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<b><a name="sns5"></a>Q: How often does Feign Death fail?</b><br>
<br>
A: After reaching Skill Level 100(Master), I would say the rate of failure is about 5%, possibly less. In these instances you receive a "[character name] has fallen to the ground" message, and the feign was never successful.  This is not a broken feign, it's a failed one.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<b><a name="sns6"></a>Q: What is my chance of memory-wiping a Mob?</b><br>
<br>
A: When feigning off mobs under level 32, Feign Death memory-wipes the mob every time it succeeds. With NPCs higher than level 32, you will usually(still have a chance of mem-wiping a mob at this level, just a much smaller chance) remain on the aggro list until they path back to their spawn point(assuming they left it to chase you) but they will ignore you if you don't stand back up. Once they reach their spawn point, they have approximately a 90% chance of forgetting you. If they do not forget you, they will have a larger aggro radius than usual with regards to you. One workaround is to camp out or use the /q feature. After a couple of minutes you can re-connect and you will know for sure you are off their hate list.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<b><a name="sns7"></a>Q: Are there any known bugs in Feign Death?</b><br>
<br>
A: There are a few known bugs, all of which are notorious for being hard to repeat and hard to fix.  Sometimes, when using the first person view, attempting to immediately stand up after feigning will cause you to be unable to move. Sitting, then standing again will clear this, but be very careful because even green mobs will aggro on you if you sit. When pulling higher-level creatures I would recommend using a third-person view anyway, so practice using both the view and the skills early.  There is also a very annoying bug which causes FD to fail with no messages sometimes when there are multiple characters on a mob's aggro list(almost all the time during grouping/raiding). This is still being researched by Verant staff, and they seem to have reduced its occurrence (though it's not been totally fixed yet).<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<b><a name="sns8"></a>Q: When I get a new special attack, should I stop using the old one?</b><br>
<br>
