<b><a name="msc4"></a>Q: What's the FD bug, and what can I do to fix it?</b><br>
<br>
A: "The FD bug" that people refer to is the one where you hit the FD key, fall over, don't get any of the various failure messages, but you still get beaten on like a madman. Some things you can do to fix it -- <br>
<br>
1. Make sure that autoattack is off when you hit FD. Make sure autoattack has been off long enough to catch up to your lag; that means waiting at least 3 seconds, if you're on a dialup or under raid lag.<br>
<br>
2. Move around a bit before you FD (unless you habitually get the "you have moved and are no longer feigning death" message). Most people jump back.<br>
<br>
3. Make sure that the failure wasn't caused by something more mundane, like a message you missed due to spam or lag.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Also, guides usually don't give rezzes for deaths due to "The FD Bug", since it's not a recognized one. Also, VI's said that they've tried to fix this one, and its occurrence has been greatly reduced since they've said it.<br>
