<b><a name="msc6"></a>Q: What is the Mend bug? </b><br>
<br>
This bug only occurs if you hit mend very soon after it has ungreyed. Upon hitting mend, instead of receiving back a quarter of your health you receive the message "You must wait 'x' seconds before you can Mend again."  X is normally between 0 and 6, however the message is a big fib, and basically if you see it, Mend greys out and you have to wait the full six minutes.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
It was fixed once, and then re-appeared recently after the Luclin launch.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
You can camp out and come back and the button will be ungreyed, if you really need to mend RIGHT NOW (i.e. to keep your spawn timing at the Raster camp).  The root cause of the bug (and any other "you must wait X seconds before you can Y again" ones) is fluctuating lag. The scenario is like this:<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
(under heavy lag)<br>
<br>
1. You hit the Mend button. Your computer starts a 6-minute timer until it ungreys Mend again, and sends a "Mend me!" packet to the EQ server.<br>
<br>
2. Several seconds pass while your "Mend me!" packet wends its way to the server.<br>
<br>
3. The server finally gets the packet, updates your health, and starts a 6-minute timer until you can mend again.<br>
<br>
4. The lag abates during the next 6 minutes.<br>
<br>
5. Your mend button ungreys, and you (being at .5bubbles with two mobs beating on you) bash it like a madman. Your computer sends a "Mend me!" packet again, and starts another timer.<br>
<br>
6. Since you're not lagging anymore, the packet gets to the server quickly-- so quickly, in fact, that it hasn't been 6 minutes since the server last recieved a "Mend me!" packet from you. Thinking that you're a hacking bastid, the server tells you you have to wait before you mend again.<br>
<br>
7. At this point, the server wouldn't mind at all getting another Mend packet from you. After all, it's been more than 6 minutes since your last Mend. But the client thinks you Mended just now, so it won't let you push the button for another 6 minutes.<br>
<br>
8. You camp out and come back. Part of this process is asking the server which skills you can use, and Mend is one of the ones you can -- so the client ungreys the button.<br>
