<b><a name="me16a"></a>Q: Should I go for hit points over everything?</b></br><br>
A: There is long a debate on HP>AC>RESIST>STAT<p><br>
<br>
Really it is going to be situational to your primary function, so you need to really sit down and decide what it is you most often find yourself doing.<p><br>
<br>
Do you solo? AC/HP is your goal (make your HP go further and get more hp. If you are soloing mobs, then you are at a level of encounters where AC still matters)<p><br>
<br>
Do you pull? HP/Resists (espicially end game, AC begins to mean squat. You will get barraged by spells however so the more you can take and the more you resist is imperative)<p><br>
<br>
Do you small group damage? Stats/haste (in most cases you are not MT (assuming you are post 30) so your role becomes damage. All else is secondary)<p><br>
<br>
Do you raid? Resists/HP (again, MTs should be doing their job so yours is to survive all collateral damage by resisting as much as possible and having the HP to endure. Yes, this puts you well suited for end game pulling as well, and that is by design.)<p><br>
<br>
Depending on what you do, is going to be your biggest push for how you stack your monk. Additionally, where your monk is at, is also reasonably important.<br><br>
